{"published time": "2024-03-18T13:29:00+08:00", "images": ["https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2022/11/drony-1-e1710761507236.jpg", "https://armyinform.com.ua/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/did-lifestory.jpg"], "content": "<div class=\"single-content\"><figure class=\"post-thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"attachment-post-thumbnail size-post-thumbnail wp-post-image\" height=\"591\" src=\"../Images/2024-03-18T13-29-00-08-00/000000.jpg\" srcset=\"../Images/2024-03-18T13-29-00-08-00/000000.jpg\" width=\"1014\"/><figcaption class=\"wp-caption-text\">Illustrative photo</figcaption></figure><!-- .post-thumbnail --><p><strong>Today, the government has allocated UAH 5 billion for security and defense forces. The funds will be directed to the purchase of drones needed for our front line defenders.</strong></p><p>About this<a href=\"https://t.me/Denys_Smyhal/7167\" rel=\"nofollow\" target=\"_blank\">reported</a>Prime Minister of Ukraine Denis Shmigal.</p><p>\u201cWe continue to support the Ukrainian army in the fight against the Russian aggressor. Every hryvnia, which comes to the state budget in the form of taxes, will go to strengthen our defense capability, \u201dthe head of government said.</p><figure class=\"kg-card ai-readalso-card\"><a class=\"ai-readalso-container\" href=\"https://armyinform.com.ua/2024/03/15/dvoma-udarnymy-dronamy-my-znyshhyly-11-vorozhyh-tankiv-komandyr-vzvodu-udarnyh-bpla-code-9-2/\" target=\"_blank\"><div class=\"ai-readalso-content\"><div class=\"ai-readalso-title\">Two shock drones we destroyed 11 enemy tanks - commander of the platoon of shock UAV Code 9.2</div></div><div class=\"ai-readalso-thumbnail\"><img alt=\"\u0414\u0432\u043e\u043c\u0430 \u0443\u0434\u0430\u0440\u043d\u0438\u043c\u0438 \u0434\u0440\u043e\u043d\u0430\u043c\u0438 \u043c\u0438\u00a0\u0437\u043d\u0438\u0449\u0438\u043b\u0438 11\u00a0\u0432\u043e\u0440\u043e\u0436\u0438\u0445 \u0442\u0430\u043d\u043a\u0456\u0432\u00a0\u2014 \u043a\u043e\u043c\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0438\u04